enhanced_by.reason: Both methods require similar input parameters such as symbol, side, quantity, and price.
Both methods involve order management and can be used to set up scenarios where orders are created and then canceled.
The getOcoOrder method can be used to verify the details of the OCO order created by the ocoOrder method.
The getAllOcoOrders method can be used to verify the list of all OCO orders, including the one created by the ocoOrder method.
